name: rb-jekyll-environment-variables
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "jekyll-environment-variables" %}
{% set version = "1.0.1" %}

package:
  name: rb-{{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://rubygems.org/downloads/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
  sha256: 4f1e287d4e659d04e0f328d6d14ded3d719ad625bd805f96f2379a5a2c7e01c3

build:
  noarch: generic
  number: 0
  script:
    - gem install -N -l -V --norc --ignore-dependencies {{ name }}-{{ version }}.gem
  skip: {{ win }}

requirements:
  host:
    - ruby
  run:
    - ruby
    - rb-jekyll >=3.0,<5

test:
  commands:
    - gem list -i {{ name }} -v {{ version }}

about:
  home: https://rubygems.org/gems/{{ name }}
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Access environment variables using Liquid tags with Jekyll

  doc_url: https://www.rubydoc.info/gems/{{ name }}
  dev_url: https://github.com/iBug/{{ name }}

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/ruby
